@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Code of Conduct";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<h2>Vision</h2>
<p>The vision of Spinney Strawberry Grove & Co. is to provide high quality produce using green and carbon neutral methods.</p>

<h2>Mission</h2>
<p>The mission of Spinney Strawberry Grove & Co. is to provide good quality produce.</p>

<h2>Core Values</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Value our people</li>
    <li>Open and honest in our dealings</li>
    <li>Innovative and commercial</li>
    <li>Enthusiastic</li>
    <li>Produce focused</li>
</ul>

<h2>Code of Conduct Overview</h2>
<p>
    This code of conduct provides clear guidance to ensure that everyone is aware of our responsibilities regarding conduct and behaviour. It translates the values into standards and behaviours we must demonstrate while performing our duties and ensures a respectful, positive, and professional working environment.
</p>
<p>
    Failure to follow the code of conduct may result in investigation and potentially disciplinary action.
</p>

<h3>Equality and Diversity</h3>
<p>
    We promote equality and value diversity. Everyone should feel welcome in our workplace. We are committed to inclusivity, innovation, and empowering all team members. We treat everyone with honesty, dignity, and respect. Bullying or harassment is not tolerated.
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Examples of harassment include offensive remarks, slurs, or jokes based on protected characteristics, inappropriate conduct, or communications via messages or social media.</li>
    <li>Report any concerning behaviour to your manager or HR. Managers must report allegations to HR immediately.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Payroll and Timekeeping</h3>
<p>Follow clocking in and out procedures:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Arrive a few minutes early</li>
    <li>Do not leave early without permission</li>
    <li>Notify manager if arriving late or unable to clock in/out</li>
</ul>
<p>Never falsify time records or clock in/out for someone else. This is considered gross misconduct.</p>

<h3>Health and Safety</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Stay alert and report hazards</li>
    <li>Know emergency procedures</li>
    <li>Report all injuries or accidents immediately</li>
    <li>Use PPE as required (e.g., high-vis vests, helmets, eye protection, coveralls)</li>
    <li>Comply with training, SOPs, risk assessments (RAs), and safe systems of work (SSOWs)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Drugs and Alcohol</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Do not work under the influence of drugs or alcohol</li>
    <li>Notify HR if seeking help with substance issues</li>
    <li>Disclose medications that may impact job performance</li>
    <li>Drink responsibly at company-sponsored events</li>
</ul>

<h3>Smoking and E-Cigarettes</h3>
<p>
    Smoking and e-cigarettes are only allowed in designated areas during approved breaks. Prohibited inside facilities or while on duty.
</p>

<h3>Behaviour and Standards</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Treat everyone with respect and professionalism</li>
    <li>No personal device use during work hours unless on break</li>
    <li>Maintain cleanliness and report any issues</li>
    <li>Follow instructions or ask for clarification</li>
</ul>

<h3>Personal Devices</h3>
<p>
    Personal devices are employee responsibility. They must not be used during work. Use of handheld devices while driving on business is not permitted.
</p>

<h3>Disclosure of Information (GDPR)</h3>
<p>
    Employees must respect the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of information. Adhere to the Data Protection Act 2018 and UK GDPR.
</p>

<h3>Off Duty</h3>
<p>
    Behaviour outside of work must not bring the company into disrepute. Do not allow private interests to conflict with your job. Appearance and conduct should reflect company values even when commuting or representing the company.
</p>

<h3>Performance of Duties</h3>
<p>
    Follow all procedures and managerial instructions related to your work.
</p>